MissionCommands.Message: Ok, we are about to get ready to start the trans-lunar injection preparations.
Roger, sounds good, we are looking into the data.
Ok, in this phase of the mission, we will execute the TLI burn. This burn is performed by the S-IVB. After the burn, we will separate from it and observe it for a bit before we alter its trajectory.
Then we will realign the IMU using P52.
Roger, let's get started. Do you have the TLI data?
Not yet. We will use the S-IVB burn planner to calculate it, then execute the burn using P15 on the AGC.
{{capsuleName}}, go ahead with the TLI preparations. Open the S-IVB tool using the Comms menu.
Then reconfigure the burn parameters so you get a Perilune of about 60 nmi alt. Set the camera to burn point and try setting the Angle of TLI departure to 18 and the Flight Time Factor to 0.4075.
Good, then press EXECUTE to close the planner. It will copy the calculations into the AGC.
TB6 requested, we will start the cockpit preparations.
Roger.
Let's do the TLI (CONCATINATED) checklist. Use the RUN feature to execute the checklist.
Starting TLI checklist.
AGC Parameters should be uplinked. Once you run P15, N33 will show the ignition time in mission elapsed time.

It should have been set automatically based on the burn tool, so just hit PRO to see N14, the planned dV of the burn. That's the velocity to be gained by the burn. Hit PRO to see the countdown and proceed with the checklist.
Roger, counting down. Proceeding with the checklist.
Ready for ignition.
Roger {{capsuleName}}, verify prograde attitude, the S-IVB/IU is in control. Use timescale if needed.
90 seconds to burn.
Allow time for the APS on the S-IVB to get into the correct attitude if you used timescale. Burn is prograde and the S-IVB will automatically ignite when the countdown reaches zero.
The IU is aligning for a prograde burn.
T -30 seconds.
Ignition!
Roger ignition, register 2 on the AGC shows the delta-V left of the burn.
The burn will last about 6 minutes. The S-IVB is doing most of the work, and soon we will be on a trajectory to the Moon.

Indeed. Let's enjoy the close proximity of Earth while it lasts. We will gradually slow down until the Moons gravity becomes larger than Earths. At that point we will accelerate again, and prepare for the Lunar Orbit Injection.
We have a long journey ahead of us.
Cutoff.
Roger cutoff.
Complete the TLI checklist.
Checklist complete.
Roger, we are on a trajectory towards the Moon, congratulations with a good burn.
Roger, when is the ETA of separating from the S-IVB?
S-IVB separation is at 3 hours and 20 minutes MET. We have scheduled an eat period now, so take a little break and let's get back to S-IVB sep and IMU realign at 3h 20min MET.
Roger, sounds good. Crew, we will perform the CSM SEPARATION PREP and the CSM SEPARATION checklists to separate.
Sounds good, let's get familiar with the checklists, soon it will be just us and the CSM for the rest of the journey.
The Lunar Module has been replaced with a LM Test Article (LTA). When separating from the S-IVB, we will maneuver to observe it, and the S-IVB before it leaves on its own journey.
Yes, still a lot of work left in this phase, but food first. Feel free to use timescale to MET 3h and 10 minutes.
You ready for the S-IVB separation maneuver?
Roger, we are ready for the procedures.
Let's prepare the EMS too. It will be good to see the dV we acquire from the maneuver. Use the RUN feature to complete and set up the dV mode of the EMS. It's under G&C REFERENCE and named dV SETUP.
Roger, good idea, let's set it up. Will use a dV of zero to just see the offset, so setting dV to 0 fps.
Checklist complete.
Ok, the next checklist is the CSM SEPARATION PREP checklist.
Starting the CSM SEPARATION PREP checklist now.
Roger. Complete the preparation.
You are free to complete the separation. Use th RUN feature on the CSM SEPARATION checklist.
When the checklists ask you to thrust forward, hold the fwd translation button (default: [H]), and while holding, trigger the separation.
Roger. Prepare for separation.
There she goes. Separation complete, translating away from it.
Great. When ready, translate back to null the EMS dV offset, so we can station-keep the S-IVB.
Good separation, when ready, set the CMC MODE to FREE, and manually center the S-IVB in the commanders window.
Remember, we are on a fuel budget, so use very slow maneuvers, let the CSM take her time rotate. Then maneuver a bit around it. We have about 10 minutes to spare for formation flying.
Roger, will do.
Ok, we have 10 minutes. Stay clear of it, recommend a minimum distance of 50 feet. If you need less time than 10 minutes, use timescale.
Ok, stay clear of the launch vehicle, the venting process will start in 2 minutes.
Venting started.
Roger, thank you for the ride, S-IVB. We are on our own now.
Sure is. And the Moon is ahead of us.
Indeed. We should do the IMU alignment.

We will use the (P52) IMU Realign checklist to complete the procedures. It's a complex checklist, so a helper checklist has been made to enable the RUN feature. Open the P52 AID: REFSMMAT checklist and press RUN.
If this is your first time running P52, I suggest you read the helper checklist description to understand the procedure. Try to be as precise as possible when performing the marks.
Roger, will do.

I suggest you also open the real (P52) IMU Realign checklist and follow the steps while the guide helps you through. My advice is to always follow the checklists even if you are using the RUN feature.
And take your time with the procedure.
Roger.
Checklist complete.
Great, let's continue the coasting towards the Moon.
If anyone wants some music for the journey, feel free to use the "jukebox". You can bring your own mix-tapes on the journey too.
Good job {{capsuleName}}, {{profileName}}. This completes this mission, and this phase of the journey.

Title: SET SAIL
Description: The crew has successfully ascended into Earth Parking Orbit and has configured the spacecraft for orbital insertion.
BriefingText:
The planned maneuvers in this phase of the mission is:
- Prepare  for TLI
- Execute the TLI burn
- Separate from the S-IVB
- Observe the S-IVB
- Perform a IMU realignment


TLI
We are about 20 minutes from TB6 (Time Base 6). TB6 is starting 9 minutes and 38 seconds before TLI ignition.
Use the TLI planner to plan the burn, then start going through the TLI (concatenated) checklist to execute the burn itself.

S-IVB separation
The S-IVB will no longer be needed and will be sent into an ecliptic orbit. After separating from it you will need to observe the S-IVB and track it.

IMU realignment
The IMU needs a realignment to remove accumulated errors in the gyros. P52 will be used to do this.
